[SN]TITLE[SN]
Firefighters tackle huge shop fire in Edinburgh

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Dozens of firefighters have been tackling a huge blaze at a snowboarding, surfing and skateboarding shop in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The fire broke out at Boardwise on Lady Lawson Street at 23:38 on Thursday.
The flats above the shop were evacuated and a couple with their baby and an elderly woman were checked over by the ambulance service.
The fire was put out by 04:18 but fire engines remained at the scene.
